# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __iter__, __next__, __len__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# All eighteen values are false; no decimal class implements the iterator
# or sequence length protocols in its own __dict__.
# decimal.Decimal is a numeric type defining many arithmetic operators
# but not the iterator/sequence protocol. Context is a precision/rounding
# configuration object; the exception subclasses are error types.
# None define __iter__, __next__, or __len__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

